DSA-001D

### **Definition:**

The sum of the first `N` natural numbers is the total of numbers from 1 to N.

(Example: 1 + 2 + 3 + ... + N)

---

### **Two Methods:**

### ðŸ”¹ Method 1: Using Formula

> Sum = n * (n + 1) / 2
> 
> 
> âœ… Fastest method, no loop needed
> 

### ðŸ”¹ Method 2: Using Loop

> Add all numbers from 1 to n using a loop
> 
> 
> âœ… Good for understanding, used in programming
> 

---

### **Flow Steps (Loop Based):**

```
Start  
â†“  
Input n  
â†“  
Set sum = 0  
Set i = 1  
â†“  
Repeat while i <= n  
    sum = sum + i  
    i = i + 1  
â†“  
Print sum  
â†“  
End
```

ðŸ’» Code

```java
import java.util.Scanner;

public class SumNatural {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();

        // Method 1: Formula
        int sum1 = n * (n + 1) / 2;
        System.out.println("Sum using formula: " + sum1);

        // Method 2: Loop
        int sum2 = 0;
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            sum2 += i;
        }
        System.out.println("Sum using loop: " + sum2);
    }
}
```

### ðŸ§  Summary Shortcut (for Copy):

- Formula: `n * (n + 1) / 2`
- Loop: i = 1 to n, add to sum
- Final print sum
